---
import { execSync } from "node:child_process";

import Header from "../components/header.astro";
import DarkModeToggle from "../components/dark-mode-toggle.astro";

const commit = execSync("git rev-parse --short HEAD").toString().trim();
const datetime = new Date().toISOString();

let baseHref = Astro.site.href.replace(/\/$/, "");
let title = 'Chatbots & Philosophy';
---
<html lang="en">
<head prefix="dcterms: http://purl.org/dc/terms/#">
	<meta charset="UTF-8">
	<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
	<meta name="version" content={commit}>
	<meta name="dcterms.modified" content={datetime}>
	<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width">
	<title>{title}</title>

	<link rel="preload" href={baseHref + "/fonts/vt323-v12-latin-regular.woff2"} as="font" type="font/woff2" crossorigin="anonymous">
	<link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="/favicon.ico" />
	<link rel="stylesheet" href={baseHref + "/style/global.css"}>
</head>
<body>
	<DarkModeToggle/>
	<main>
		<Header/>
		<article>
   	  <p>The aim of this exercise is:<br>
			&nbsp; 1) to show how pre-machine learning chatbots react to user input; and<br>
			&nbsp; 2) to get a feel for how chatbots progressed before the arrival of transformer models.</p>

			<p>We have chosen three classic chatbots: Eliza (1966), Alice (1995), Kuki (2005).</p>

			<ol>
				<li>Please agree as a group on five prompts that you enter in each chatbot.</li>
				<li>We suggest you use the same five with all chatbots so you can compare the results.</li>
				<li>Use different types of prompts: Statement, question, math task, metaphor etc.</li>
			</ol>
		</article>
		<footer>
		  This page was built with Astro.build and ships zero Javascript.
		  <a href="https://github.com/simonwiles/chatbots-and-philosophy-site" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
				<svg
					xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
					aria-label="GitHub"
					role="img"
					viewBox="0 0 512 512">
					<rect width="512" height="512" rx="15%"></rect>
					<path
						d="M335 499c14 0 12 17 12 17H165s-2-17 12-17c13 0 16-6 16-12l-1-50c-71 16-86-28-86-28-12-30-28-37-28-37-24-16
							 1-16 1-16 26 2 40 26 40 26 22 39 59 28 74 22 2-17 9-28 16-35-57-6-116-28-116-126 0-28 10-51 26-69-3-6-11-32 3-67
							 0 0 21-7 70 26 42-12 86-12 128 0 49-33 70-26 70-26 14 35 6 61 3 67 16 18 26 41 26 69 0 98-60 120-117 126 10 8 18
							 24 18 48l-1 70c0 6 3 12 16 12z">
					</path>
				</svg>
			</a>

		</footer>
	</main>
</body>

</html>
